The White House will hold a briefing with senior administration officials to discuss President Obama's upcoming trip to Guadalajara, Mexico. The officials include National Security Advisor General Jim Jones, Deputy National Security Advisor for Counterterrorism and Homeland Security John Brennan, Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economic Affairs and Development Mike Froman, and NSC Senior Director for Western Hemisphere Affairs Dan Restrepo. The briefing will take place in the James S. Brady Briefing Room at the White House at 5:45PM EDT. It is open press, and journalists can request clearance by emailing their personal information to pressclearance@who.eop.gov.